==English==
===Etymology===
From [[nucleo-]] (relating to the [[nucleus]]) + [[-ide]] (chemical suffix)
===Noun===
{{wikipedia}}
'''nucleotide'''
#the monomer comprising [[DNA]] or [[RNA]] [[biopolymer]] [[molecule]]s. It consists of a nitrogenous [[heterocyclic]] [[base]] (or [[nucleobase]]), which can be either a double-ringed [[purine]] or a single-ringed [[pyrimidine]]; a five-carbon [[pentose]] [[sugar]] ([[deoxyribose]] in [[DNA]] or [[ribose]] in [[RNA]]); and a [[phosphate]] group.
